Q20: Gringo is a term that has many different meanings and connotations depending on which latino uses it. Mexicans usually use gringo to describe someone who is American, Peruvians use gringo to describe anyone who is white or white passing (specifically light hair+light eyes) and it is not limited to foreigners. We even call fellow peruvians "gringo" affectionately, if they are white/white passing. Some other latinos use "gringo" as a blanket term for "foreigner" or even as a term for diaspora latinos who don't have a connection to their roots or language.
